## PART IX — PRIOR ART PRESERVATION

### Section 26. Prior Art Record

**26.1** The Operator maintains an append-only Prior Art Record as a component
of the Sovereign Registry. The Prior Art Record is distinct from the Bound
Work registry; it records the provenance of mathematical derivations, not
just implementations.

**26.2** A Prior Art Entry consists of:

| Field | Required | Description |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| Entry ID | Yes | Unique, immutable identifier |
| Originating Maker | Yes | Legal name or pseudonym of the human who derived the mathematics |
| Title | Yes | Name of the theorem, proof, algorithm, or derivation |
| Timestamp | Yes | Unix epoch of first publication or filing, anchored to a public cryptographic commitment (git commit hash, Zenodo DOI, WORM chain seal) |
| Anchor Hash | Yes | Blake3 or SHA-256 hash of the original source file or proof object |
| Anchor URI | Yes | Publicly verifiable URL (GitHub commit, Zenodo DOI, IPFS CID) |
| Description | Yes | Plain-language summary of the mathematical content |
| Formalization | Optional | Lean 4 / Coq / Isabelle proof file, if machine-checked |
| Verification Status | Yes | One of: `CLAIMED`, `WITNESSED`, `MACHINE-CHECKED`, `CONSTITUTIONAL` |

**26.3** A Prior Art Entry is immutable once filed. It may be supplemented
(e.g., machine-checked status may be upgraded) but the original timestamp,
anchor hash, and Originating Maker fields may never be altered.

**26.4** Filing a Prior Art Entry does not create any exclusive right in the
mathematics described. The substrate remains free. The Prior Art Entry records
who derived it first and how it can be verified.

### Section 27. Foundry-F1 Prior Art Entries

**27.1** The following Prior Art Entries are hereby recorded as of the
Effective Date of this License, with cryptographic anchors on record
at the Sovereign Registry:

