## PART XI — FORENSIC ATTRIBUTION BURDEN

### Section 31. Burden of Independent Derivation

**31.1** Any Derivative Proof — a formal proof, theorem, algorithm, or
mathematical derivation that overlaps in substance with a Prior Art Entry —
is presumed to have been derived from the Prior Art Entry unless the party
asserting independent derivation affirmatively demonstrates otherwise.

**31.2** The presumption in Section 31.1 applies when:

> **(a)** The Derivative Proof was published after the Prior Art Entry
> timestamp; AND

> **(b)** The mathematical content overlaps to a degree that could not
> plausibly arise from independent derivation of elementary principles
> without intermediate copying.

**31.3** To rebut the presumption, the party asserting independent derivation
must produce:

> **(a)** A documented derivation chain — contemporaneous notes, drafts,
> or intermediate proof states — showing the mathematical development step
> by step without reference to any Formed Work covered by this License;

> **(b)** Witness testimony or independent corroboration that the mathematics
> was developed without access to the Prior Art Entry; OR

> **(c)** A machine-checked proof in Lean 4, Coq, or Isabelle/HOL submitted
> to the Technical Review Panel for independent verification, with a
> provenance certificate from the proof assistant system confirming the
> proof was developed in an isolated environment.

**31.4** The burden in Section 31.3 is on the party asserting independent
derivation. Failure to meet it sustains the presumption that the Derivative
Proof was derived from the Prior Art Entry.

**31.5** The Technical Review Panel is the arbiter of whether the burden has
been met. Panel determinations are final within the Sovereign Registry system,
without prejudice to any party's rights in any external legal proceeding.

### Section 32. Application to Foundry-F1

**32.1** Any party who publishes, files, or claims originality for a formal
proof of any of the following must meet the forensic attribution burden of
Section 31.3 or acknowledge the applicable Prior Art Entry:

- (a) The GKN quartic invariant I4 on the 56-dimensional E7 representation (PAR-001)
- (b) Homogeneity of I4 to any degree on any state space (PAR-001, PAR-002)
- (c) E7 Weyl group invariance of I4 under signed permutation representations (PAR-003)
- (d) The simplex normalization constraint formalized in Lean 4 (PAR-004)
- (e) The Bifrost attestation protocol receipt format (PAR-005)
- (f) The plasma gate + Datalog two-layer classification architecture (PAR-006)
- (g) The fused U·ρ·U† kernel architecture with inline attestation (PAR-007)

**32.2** This Section applies regardless of whether the party is a Maker,
a fork, a downstream derivative, or an independent researcher who had
access to the Formed Works at any time.

**32.3** Nothing in this Section prevents independent researchers from
publishing proofs of the same mathematical facts. The Prior Art Record
records who derived it first; it does not prohibit subsequent proofs.
What it prohibits is claiming to have derived it first without meeting
the burden of Section 31.3.

